    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "557f42c4_3334bbda",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/base/threads/WorkerThread.h",
        "patchSetId": 23
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-18T21:32:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "finish() doesn\u0027t look like it\u0027s waiting for pending items to complete (to me), it seems to be a command to finish work. Should it be a longer name, like \"waitForQueuedItems()\"?\n\nOverall, this is a dangerous API as it doesn\u0027t specify if we\u0027re waiting for items queued until the call to complete, or all of them, and what happens if there\u0027s another thread that keeps sending work.\n\nIMO it\u0027s safer for a specific user to queue some item that would implement a \"synchronization point\" when executed",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 83,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 83,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "b1ec851d9b070e9ff79331fd2d5eb5462acd989f",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
