        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-18T21:32:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what\u0027s the sense in having a separate thread if all commands are synchronized?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1679,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 1679,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "b1ec851d9b070e9ff79331fd2d5eb5462acd989f",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8c7acf3d_2578e5b6",
        "filename": "android/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/FrameBuffer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 23
      },
      "lineNbr": 1679,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-19T16:20:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s because this will be used from app threads like video encoders; it needs to have a OpenGL context, which is not guaranteed to be available or setup the right way from any other thread. Also opengl with its thread specificness :D",
      "parentUuid": "f6493e97_883ed8e7",
